Until 1989 there were in the Czechoslovakia of then only five authorized state travel agencies: Čedok, Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autoturist.
The travel agencies of that moment were selling in most cases travel only to the socialistic block, since the trips to Occident were very restricted.
