Climatic adversity braked the economy
During the first year of management of Mario López Valdez, in Sinaloa the unemployment and the informality has increased, it lowered the foreign investment and it contracted the economy
2011 is one year that will be remembered in the Sinaloa economic history, it is a question of the first year of Government of Mario López Valdez, autonamed of the change, which generated big expectations with regard to the advances in the economy, but given the climatic adversity of the beginning of the year, growth is not observed, on the other hand yes a deterioration registers in the main indicators of economic development.
The low February temperatures, in addition to causing millionaire losses for the agricultural sector, limited the possibilities of the state economy to grow, caused a contraction of the economic activity in general of 3.6 per cent in the first semester of the year, justified principally by the 31.16 per cent historical fall in the agriculture, which affected the dynamism of other economic sectors.
In accordance with the affectations report as the frosts, expressed by the Mexican Advice for the Rural development Sustentable, damages were had in 582 thousand 835 cultivated hectares, of which 78.03 per cent they incurred entire loss and the remainder 21.07 per cent had partial damage, the main damaged cultivation was those of vegetables, corn and chick-pea.
The fall in the economic activity has generated, until November, a constant increase of the unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography the valuation of state unemployment during the first three trimesters of the year observed an intensive growth, since while from January until March 55 thousand 053 sinaloenses were vacated, with a valuation of 4.53 per cent of the Population Económicamente Activa, for the second trimester the valuation happened to be a 5.28 per cent, and between July and September the average kept on increasing up to 6.19 per cent, a valuation that in number of persons throws more than 74 thousand sinaloenses unemployed men, an increase with regard to the first semester of 18 thousand 969 individuals.
Less liquidity
The unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, for the economist Gerardo López Cervantes, the director of the faculty of Economic and Social Sciences of the UAS, the growth of the unemployment can be explained by implication, according to the actions that from the public politics have been realized.
"What is seen is a growth of the unemployment that has to do with several factors, between them the loss of liquidity on the market for effects of a restriction of resources for the legislation that was approved in the congress to fight the money wash, already for the people who seizes dollars of an illicit way it is not easy to him that it them works, invests them and should use them in anything", it expressed.
Arrested migration
López Cervantes pointed out that in the increase in the unemployment a demographic factor exists also.
"The number of persons that goes away of the state in search of work abroad, in the United States has been restricted, firstly for the difficulties of entering, and second because entering already they have also many difficulties of finding work, these people are remaining and are demanding work sources here in the state, what does that the unemployment rises", it showed.
Informality
The labor market analysis sinaloense worsens on having considered the high level of informality that prevails between the working conditions, according to the INEGI, 60.38 per cent of the working population at the state are employed without being quote like worker before any social security institution.
In addition to the unemployment and informality, other of the labor backlogs of the state there are the low wages, the entity has the lowest remunerations of the Country, in accordance with the records of the Mexican Institute of the Welfare and the Secretariat of the Work and Social Forecast.
The average monthly revenue of the workpeople sinaloenses was, until September, 5 thousand 352 pesos, much underneath of the national average located in 7 thousand 375 pesos.
Contraction of IED
In addition to the fall of the economic activity and the increase in the unemployment, during 2011 there registers the biggest decrease of the Direct Foreign investment of last 10 years, according to the Treasury Department from January until June of the state IED it added 630 thousand 697 dollars, what represents a 87.74 per cent fall with regard to 5 million 143 thousand 312 dollars registered during the same period of the previous year.
For his part, the Secretariat of Economic Development of the state Government takes into account an entire investment of 17 thousand 280 millions in weight in the year, happened principally of companies of the service industries.
The debt
Before the stage of economic contraction, the Government of the state requested in July to the state congress the approval of a credit for 3 billions in weight, themselves that they would be destined the investment in projects of infrastructure in 18 municipalities, for the purpose of reactivating the economy, the approval of the local congress was for a total of 2 thousand 600 millions in weight, and until November they have not observed the benefits of the indebtedness in any sector of the state economy.
Reactions
For representatives of the managerial sector, the first year of Government of Mario López Valdés gives sample of an absence of capacity of management of the Government.
Miguel Loredo López, president of the National Chamber of the Industry of the Transformation, expressed that during 2011 one lacked the harmonization of wills of the different sectors, including to the proper Government of the state.
"The performance of the economy in Sinaloa during this year has been really very poor, it is necessary to work intensely to recover the area that we lost in this year, in 2012 we have to redouble efforts, it was lacking to align the effort of all and especially the already synchronized good march of this new team of Government, we hope that next year should be much better", it expressed.
Economic slowness
Loredo López showed that events as the frosts of the beginning of the year stopped the state economy and restricted its performance and growth.
"The low economic flow is a product of several events, between them the frosts, one of the main effects has been a slow economy that the sufficiently rapid thing does not turn round to generate an economic dynamism that allows to have an acceptable flow level in the processes, products and services and therefore, at the end of the year we are closing much underneath of the expectations that we had", it mentioned.
To re-define vocation
For Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, president of the Management Confederacy of the Mexican Republic in Sinaloa, it showed that it is needed to prosecute the state towards productive activities of major dynamism.
"In general terms we have observed that one has been working, we believe that it is necessary to develop a program of long term in which there is re-defined the vocation and the economic course of the state, because it is important that one detonates the whole potential of the material and human resource that Sinaloa has", he said.
I work for doing
The president of the Coparmex emphasized the importance of establishing a vision of future that channels better the efforts of the Government.
"In general terms I would say that the Government has been straining for giving good results in different matters, on the subject of economic development there are some advances but it is important that a long-term program develops", it showed.
It pointed out that the current administration has showed advances in its way of leading the public politics.
"There are elements that they allow to say that the Government is more enclosing, I what I can say is that there is made work and I believe that the Government is conscious of that there is work for doing", it expressed.
