Asphalt of the UNAM would avoid holes
Rafael Herrera, investigator of the faculty of Chemistry of the UNAM, develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a miscellany with better performance, independently of the environmental conditions and of temperature
If the signs that the paving sends should attend, it would not be necessary to repair nearly 200 thousand holes every raining season in the Metropolitan area of the Vale of Mexico, warned Rafael Herrera Nájera, investigator of the faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, who made sure that if the process of construction and maintenance of an asphalt paving is the suitable one, the holes might diminish in quantity or, enclosed, be eliminated completely.
In its conference A technological opinion about the holes, dictated in the frame of the International Year of the Chemistry, announced that the laboratory to its charge develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a miscellany with characteristics similar to those of the asphalt, but with a major mechanical resistance, so much to high as to low temperatures.
Farrier Nájera thought that this type of modified asphalts might be used in places where the climate is extremely warm, like some cities of the north of the country, to improve its performance and, therefore, the formation of holes.
He told that the asphalt, the heaviest part of the oil, is a set of molecules of hydrocarbons, some of high molecular weight, calls asfaltenos, and others of low molecular weight, calls maltenos, that meetings give him to the paving its characteristic behavior viscoelástico.
The behavior viscoelástico of the asphalt consists of the fact that to high temperatures, close to 180 grades, behaves like a liquid, to 120 degrees centigrade its stickiness is very high and to 50 degrees centigrade it presents the almost solid state, while to very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes fragile, it added.
The previous thing means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform, but it is modified during the day in accordance with the environmental conditions and of temperature, warned the specialist in chemical engineering.
The investigator of the FQ observed that the streets of the Mexico City mostly are covered by flexible paving, which consists of six layers of materials, of which the last three involve to the asphalt.
Between the most superficial layers there is the asphalt folder shaped by small stones bathed in asphalt and then compactadas.
Each of the piedritas who constitutes the folder, it pointed, is bathed by asphalt.
After the vehicles to journey and after efforts are generated, this one allows the forces to spread very well in the paving.
If it was a question of modified asphalt they would spread even better, thought the chemical engineer.
On the asphalt folder, it abounded, there places a last layer called folder of rolling, which is done of a thin stone material, that is to say, a sand that also bathes in asphalt.
Since it is a question of the layer that is going to be in contact with the rims of the vehicles, it must have more mechanical force that the asphalt folder and to provide friction in the way.
The part of the paving that is going to receive and spread the efforts, the rolling folder needs from the being, also, to have the suitable thickness and it is necessary to take care of the material of the one that is made.
The climate, especially the moisture and the changes of temperature, also there are a very important factor to be considered, especially the water, he said, because it affects greatly the performance of the asphalt folder.
When the area becomes damp, the water spreads inside the folder and it is difficult that it goes out, this causes a softening of all the layers of the paving and, therefore, the formation of holes.
In the process of formation of a hole, he said, the first one in getting worn is the bearing movie and only later the asphalt folder falls ill, but the damage does not happen instantaneously, but it is a process that should be attended on the first signs with suitable maintenance programs.
Also member of the National System of Investigators told that the transport load is another important factor in the holes formation and, for it, the thickness of each of the layers of the paving must always go as regards the transport load and guarantee that it is fulfilled, to prevent from forming holes often.
Rafael Herrera warned that it still exists much that to investigate and to work on the asphalt, for example, the asphalt emulsions, which in other countries are already enclosed on the market and allow to repair the holes with facility and without need to use high temperatures.
