The Government of big coalition socialdemócrata/democratacristiano that is in the power in Austria has decided on Tuesday to include in the Constitution a "budgetary rule of gold" to reduce the budget deficit and, this way, to avoid a possible degradation of the sovereign note of Austria on the part of the agencies of credit qualification (triple A).
It was the proper social-democratic Chancellor, Werner Faymann, who announced this decision after a Cabinet, when the Austrian public debt reaches 74,6 %, a number very superior to the maximum limit of 60 % fixed by the Treaty of Maastrich, but clearly lower than the countries debts like Italy, Greece or Spain.
"If the solvency of Austria was diminishing in only one level, from AAA to AA +, we would have to pay 3.000 million euros more in interests every year", pointed out the Vice chancellor democratacristiano of Foreign affairs, Michael Spindelegger.
Austria answers this way to a request of the Summit of Brussels to the member countries of the area of the euro of last October 26: in her, the heads of state and of Government asked for the inclusion, before ends of 2012, of the reduction of the budget deficit and of the recovery of the balance of the public accounts in the Constitution or in a Law with equivalent value.
The device adopted as the Austrian Government comes closer the "German model", since Germany was the first European country that adopted this type of "rule".
Before 2017, the structural budget deficit should diminish every year in 0,75 % of the Gross National Product (GDP) and, from 2017, the structural budget deficit of the federal State should not overcome every year 0,35 % of the GDP, while the regional States, as well as the communes, should present balanced budgets.
