As there point out the economists Ian Goldin and Geoffrey Cameron in a recent work that he sums the most recent knowledge up on the immigration (Exceptional People: How Migration Shaped Our World and Will Define Our Future, May, 2011, Princeton University Press, 352 pp)., a wide consensus exists between the specialists on the positive impact of the migratory flows in the economic growth, the wages and the employment in the countries that immigrants receive.
