The immigrants also are clear taxpayers to the social systems, since they contribute of average a 1 % of the entire budget in the European countries.
The International organization of the Work calculates, for example, that in Germany an immigrant who comes with an age of 30 years will realize a clear contribution (income less expenses) for 150.000 euros to the public average budgets during all its life.
At the beginning of its order, Nicolas Sarkozy wanted to go to look for the points of growth that he was lacking "with the teeth".
The above mentioned teeth, which dissuaded the immigrants, had exactly the inverse effect.
