Nord Stream, new door of entry of the Russian gas in Europe
The gas pipeline Nord Stream, which communicates straight western Europe with Russia spending for the bottom of the sea Baltic, has already put itself in service.
It must give gas to satisfy the needs for thirty million hearths.
Gazprom, the Russian giant of the gas, has wanted to celebrate the event with big pomp.
Last Tuesday, more than 500 guests, including four heads of state and of Government, informed on the banks of the Baltic, between the music of the band and a delicate buffet, in the opening of Nord Stream, the new gas pipeline that communicates straight, under the sea, Russia with Germany.
Symbolically, German chancellor Angela Merkel, the Russian President Dmitri Medvedev, the French Prime minister François Fillon and its counterpart of the Netherlands, Mark Rutte, have turned together the frill of the valve that controls the entry of Russian gas in the network of western Europe.
With this new gas pipeline, there will come every year 27,5 million additional cubic meters of Russian gas to western Europe across the first one it had of 1.224 km that communicate the region of Saint Petersburg with Land de Mecklemburgo-Pomerania.
The second pipe should end at the end of 2012 that will allow to give a whole of 55.000 million cubic meters of gas, that is to say, sufficiently to cover the whole French consumption.
Also, already one speaks about the possibility of constructing a third pipe for the same trip.
For Gazprom, the ending on time of this enormous work presents victory airs.
Poland and the Baltic countries had been opposed firmly to the project.
In fact, Nord Stream is going to allow to give gas straight Germany, avoiding the terrestrial course for third countries (Poland and Ukraine).
Suddenly, these two countries lose something of its power: for them, it will be more difficult to influence in Russia threatening her to close the access to the markets of western Europe.
In the icy point of the debate, Warsaw did not hesitate to compare the Nord Stream as a German - Soviet "new agreement", in reference to the alliance between Hitler and Stalin to occupy Poland in 1939.
Namely if the topic is politically delicate.
Western Europe, supporting the Russian project, has obtained a major supply safety.
But the price is a weakening of the Europe of the energy, since the project has generated a breach between the Europeans of this one and of the west.
Russia has been able, in only five years, to make triumph its vision of a direct alliance between Russia and the rich, big western countries consuming gas and with a few more and more limited reservations.
"This gas pipeline constitutes a component of our association with Russia, a new artery that joins us of organic form", confirmed François Fillon during the opening of the gas pipeline, demonstrating until point the big contracts of the sector of the gas are so political as economic.
All this explains the wide smiles in the faces of the managers of Gazprom, numerous in Lubmin, in the point of arrival of the gas.
The construction of this gas pipeline also supposes a technical achievement.
The submarine pipe is made of steel covered with cement to protect it against the anchors of the ships.
It rests at the bottom of the sea, to an average 200 m deep.
To construct it, it was necessary to avoid minefields that date back to the Second World war.
"It was necessary to withdraw or to destroy a hundred of them, for precaution", points out Jens Müller, spokesman of the society Nord Stream.
Also, it turned out to be necessary to carry to extremes the protection measurements of the fauna and the flora.
The pipe is a long snake of metal that weighs like 242 towers Eiffel and is not interrupted in all its length: not neither for valves, nor for stations of maintenance.
A control platform was foreseen in the waters of Sweden, but the persons in charge of the project resigned the same one on having seen that the Swedishes were not very ready to allow a Russian state society to settle of permanent form in the sea opposite to its coasts.
"In case of breakdown, we will interrupt the step of the gas in less than one minute", adds Jens Müller.
In case of escape, the gas of the gas pipeline will be liberated, therefore, to the ambience.
But the builders consider little to be probable that should produce an escape to himself, since they have foreseen junctions that, according to the forecasts, will have an escape every 100.000 years.
The control of the state of the gas pipeline is guaranteed by means of a submarine robot dragged by a ship, which realizes exterior examinations, as well as by means of a device that circulates along the interior of the gas pipeline.
With the form of a cigar, it interferes inside the pipe, which possesses an one meter diameter, and moves with the gas.
At its arrival, after three full time of trip to a three meters speed per second, it gives precise information on possible distortions of the metal.
The gas pipeline has been designed to work for fifty years without need of any type of repair.
The circulation of the gas is guaranteed simply by the pressure.
At first it is 200 bars and, to the exit of 100 bars.
Five companies have joined its forces to be able to carry out this project.
The leading corporation is a Gazprom, which 51 % of the shares possesses.
To her, there joined the Germans E.ON and BASF (15,5 % each one), as well as the Dutchwoman Gasunie and the French group GDF Suez (9 % each one).
These five societies have created a common company, called Nord Stream, manager of constructing and exploiting the gas pipeline.
It has its head office in Zoug, Switzerland, where the imposition turns out to be especially favorable.
Later, Gazprom rented to the above mentioned society, during a renewable term of twenty-five years, the totality of the capacities of gas transport.
"He will pay away from Gazprom for the entire capacity, independently of the gas quantity that really is transported", adds Jens Müller.
The financing of the construction of the gas pipeline has taken I finish in 30 % with the contribution of the shareholders and in 70 % by means of bank loans.
The entire cost of the work should reach 7.400 million euros for two pipes.
For GDF Suez, for example, the investment has reached 240 millions.
But the minority shareholders are sure that they will not overcome its investment, since Gazprom assumes himself the risk of the expenses.
The gas pipeline emerges of the Baltic in Lubmin, on a planted sandy pines coast.
A few valves, with 4,5 meters high, form the door of exit of the gas.
There exist a few sensors that measure the pressure, the temperature and the specific characteristics of the gas at the arrival, before it is transferred to the German gas pipelines.
From the last Tuesday, the terminal receives a million cubic meters of Russian gas every hour.
To entire capacity, there will be three millions per hour and in 2012, six millions.
