Making use of its success and cultural aura is, Moleskine has been able to diversify its products: purses, agendas, pens, cases of computer... The mark includes a wide range of supports.
A success that provokes envy: in autumn 2006, Way Way was acquired by the investment fund Cardinal SG Europe, at present Cardinal Syntegra, writing to him this way a new page in the Moleskine history.
Why does the valuation of unemployment of the disabled workpeople keep on being so high?
About 19 % of the disabled persons is looking for an employment.
XV Week for the employment of the disabled ones starts today.
In spite of a decisive public politics, applied from 2005, the unemployment valuation between the disabled persons duplicates the average valuation: 19 %, opposite to 9 % for the set of the population.
Discouraging?
"No", affirms Éric Blanchet, director-general of Adapt, the association that organizes the week for the employment of the disabled ones.
"The progresses reached for fifteen years are considerable.
"Then, the unemployment valuation was not two times but three times higher than the average.
"Nevertheless, very much still stays for doing".
It is necessary to mention that the disabled unemployed men keep on facing numerous obstacles to gain access to the employment.
They usually have a more advanced age: 37 % has more than 50 years (17 % of average).
They possess a slightly high qualification level: 80 % has not finished the baccalaureate and, of 2,3 million students in the higher education, only 10.000 are disabled.
Finally, the unemployment of long duration is much extended between them: 53 % for the disabled ones, opposite to 38 % of average.
Namely there exist numerous questions that make difficult especially the return to the labor world and that "they constitute the core of the problem", points out Christian Grapin, director-general of Tremplin, an association created in 1992 to help the companies to hire disabled workpeople.
These are the objective obstacles.
Also, there exist those that are not mentioned; the mentality of the people advances, but too slowly.
A study realized in April by the association IMS-Entreprendre for the Cité was pointing out that the polled directors have "a knowledge level on the disabilities under", with a "excessive representation of the persons in wheelchair, deficient physicists or intellectuals".
The result: the private enterprises with more than 20 workers are very far from the target to hire 6 % of disabled workpeople, target that was fixed in a law of... 1987.
According to the last available numbers, which date of 2008, they reach a relation of 2,6 %.
"Now we reach concerning 3 %", points out Pierre Blanc, director-general of Agefiph, the organism entrusted to collect the contributions of the companies that do not respect this law.
The test: the number of establishment "submitted to this contribution", as the paid out quantities, they have diminished between 2007 and 2011, spending from 59.000 to 46.000 structures (and from 606 to 480 million euros).
"The law of 2005, which was increasing the contributions, has generated a big pressure for the companies", tells Pierre Blanc.
"But this progress also reflects a real campaign to raise public awareness, in particular between the big groups".
According to the Department of Labour, only 59 % of the societies who possess between 20 and 49 workers account with disabled personnel in its staff, opposite to 82 % of the companies of between 100 and 199 workers.
